{
  "text": "Through the slope tool, the model of slope was created, according to the procedure described in [65] . A maximum slope of 15% was established following the methodology in [CITATION_1] . The location of the wood storage yards should be in a flat, well-drained area. Up to 15% is close to corrugated areas according to [65] ; this value was adopted by [CITATION_2] and considered feasible in the present work. Areas above the established value were considered restricted for the allocation of storage yards. Subsequently, the reclassification was carried out with a value for suitable areas of 1 and a value of 10 for unsuitable areas. As such, values greater than10 represent areas unsuitable for the allocation of wood storage yards.",
  "citation_candidates": [
    "103671413",
